Aight folks, help with some cuts. Mana curve in particular is very, very high. Do your worst.
huh, I was wondering what you thought about wake the dead joey
I found it last night in my collection and thought it was interesting
I don’t like it in regular reanimator because I prefer to keep the creatures, but in a deck full of death triggers I’ve been pretty pleased
totally, I was thinking of putting it in gonti to be honest, there are times when I get a little greedy and put him in my yard but don't really have a way to get him out soon
hm, I'm only seeing 11 token makers.... not completely sure if if anoited is going to be the best.... no I take that back, most are pretty repeateable here
oh wait, no the number goes up, missed that treasures are tokens at first
requiem angel is fin, but expensive for what you're doing
revel in riches is something I have in my breya deck but I'm honestly going to remove it before this weekend, it's fun for a while but not great

You’re converging on a lot of he same cards as me, actually. My current thoughts for cuts: 


Divine Visitation
Anointed procession
Harvest of souls 
Requiem angel
Sun titan
Krav 
Regna 
Dark prophecy
Read the Bones
I do think you have enough redunecy in creature form to cut dark proph
I hate to see read the bones go though

I think it might cut Grave Pact if you’re already running Dictate. I can get behind running one at least, and they can be especially oppressive with Teysa. Devoting two slots to that seems a bit much when you could use that slot to smooth your deck instead.
I think you might add Priest of Forgotten Gods
my biggest thought right now on the deck is that you are paying life for repeated effect, the only way I see you gaining life is with things like zulaport cutthroat
And blood artist and cruel celebrant and kokusho and tokens have vigilance and lifelink
Confession time, I think priest of forgotten gods is pretty trash :open_mouth:
But--convince me!
Where have you seen/tried it?
oh shoot, that legendary, sac two to bring back a duder
whisper
Whisper
that would be beyond great here
I’m not a fan of Priest either
I have a general resistance to creatures with tap effects
So you haven't?
There are also 32 creatures in the deck already
thats fair joey, I'm just trying to think of ways that you'd finish the game in a board stall
fine to have more than 32 creatures if the commander refers to having other creatures
Joey, have you seen it in action at all?

No, I haven't, though I haven't seen Liliana's Triumph in action either and I know I don't want that card, too. Not a direct comparison, I'm just saying gut instinct counts for something.

Priest looks like mediocre ramp, mediocre removal, and mediocre draw, and slow at all three
I'm kinda iffy on ministrant of obligation... the price is pretty decent but.... eeehhhhhh
It's been pretty :fire: in the games I've played it in. It's a repeatable edict on a stick.
With upside.
Ministrant and Flesh Carver have been on my watch list, yeah
Summoning sickness makes it slow I suppose, but once you've had it a turn it does some work.
the nice thing about flesh carver though is that it makes a token when it leaves and is a sac outlet though
Do you see much voltron in your playgroup Joey?
he just doesn't like your card, dean.

If I ran Priest I would be tempted to try out Whisper, which opens the door also to Victimize

Not particularly much Voltron, no
but then again, hallowed spirit keeper is basically militiant but with a higher ceiling and a lower floor
I mean, they're all cheap. You can try them and cut them with relative ease.
Still leaves the question of what to cut from the list above :wink:
True!
I think I agree with divine visitiation cut
Is Harvester of Souls still on the list? I'm not a fan of that card at the cmc

My current cuts list:

Divine Visitation
Anointed procession
Harvest of souls
Requiem angel
Sun titan
Krav
Regna
Dark prophecy
Read the Bones
I also think Reliquary Monk might be too cute
"why aren't you running armegeddon?" - don
Why is tombstone stairwell in here? Just sac fodder? I think cut that. Revel of riches is too slow imo. Dictate of erebos is too expensive at 5 cmc i think
that's what I always think too don, but people always argue with me...
I would argue to run Dictate over Grave Pact 9 time’s out of 10
Suns champion is meh
I don't like Cathars' Crusade just because it's a math class every time
Tombstone Stairwell was introduced to me by Cameron on our show coming out tomorrow, I wanna try it. Tokens with haste vigilance and lifelink and tons of death triggers every turn sound delightful
Interesting
He didn't suggest it as a cEDH pick, mind you, just a funny card that looks stupid but does stupid stuff too
Yeah
I'm surprised to hear you don't like elspeth
Have you thought about Dawn of the Dead?
I know it's done work for Matt
I like it but you have a lot of cuts to make
Sorry, that's not a cut...
I dont like your 3cmc rocks.
Esp since your commander is 4 mana
Id cut both
Oh, yeah, this is a 2 color deck
I don't think Lantern belongs here.
I'm also not a huge fan of Ashnod's Altar since you're running Phyrexian
oh god didn't notice lantern, yeah it goes out
it's really not needed in 2 color decks
The density of double white and triple black was the main concern
I don't even run it in all my 3 color decks.
Thoughts on Regna and Krav? I feel like they're either amazing or deeply terrible
I was surprised you cut them. I feel like they're strong in this deck.
I'm not sure if you have  enough easy to repeat life gain for regna
In general, I've fallen way out of love with Harvester of Souls, there are just way better options at 3 mana.
All his tokens have lifelink.
I guess?
Yeah, he's already running Liliana at the same CMC, and Haruspex and Reaper.
[[mimic vat]] would be hilarious

text: Deck was heavy on the tokens for a while. Mimic Vat, Helm of the Host. Was pretty unwieldy though
For the record I love Mimic Vat here, I just wanna know what to cut before I add all the cards I like :smile:
Requiem Angel also seems pricy for the effect.
that's on the chopping block already
And it's been mentioned, but I'm also not crazy about the 3 mana rocks, especially when you're not playing some of the creature options for mana.
Like Knight of the White Orchid and such, you mean?
Boreas Charger?
That works too, but I was more thinking Crypt Ghast
Although I personally would want to try out [[Cathodian]] just to see...
I'm surprised no one has come to the defense of Sun Titan on my potential cuts list
[[Cathodion]]

text: No, stop, don't cut it.
(seriously, it recurs your noncreature sac outlets and stuff)
Sun & Grave Titans end up cut for me all the time.
I'm not big on Grave Titan, though
6 mana is just a lot.
That's so weird. I feel much more strongly about Grave than Sun. Those extra bodies get good. Sun titan feels.... okay.
I'm all about those graveyard loops. Sac and recur
Sun Titan is better for that than Grave Titan
Grave titan kills people. Sun titan annoys them.
I guess.
I don't run Grave Titan in a single deck.
I’d dump both dictates/edicts. You’re in white and black so you can remove anything and you don’t need the lock pieces.
Honestly, what’s your goal, <@U3MTJRAQL>?
yeah, that would help some
like, ideally, how do you win with the deck?

Initial plan was a token swarm, but that's faded some. Plenty of wins will still involve that, I'm sure, but the repeated artisocrat death triggers are getting a lot more focus. Some combination of those - beat people with a bunch of creatures, and if they kill them, it hurts them instead of me
sadness tokens
Y'know...
This might actually be a deck for [[Maw of the Obzedat]]

If you’re off the token swarm, you definitely need to drop down the enchantment count, like Cathars, Anointed procession, Dictate of Erebos, Grave Pact, Revel.
cathars should deffinitly be out with swarm idea as secondary
anoited is border line, dictate and grave pact are whatever, revel is is just gonna be not great
